### Restaurant Reservation API — sample requests
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### --- Auth ---

### Register
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "john",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "Secret123!"
}

### Login (demo user)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "demo",
  "password": "User123!"
}

### Login (admin)
# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "Admin123!"
}

### --- Tables (public) ---

### Available tables
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/tables/available?dateTime=2026-05-20T19:00:00&duration=90&guestCount=4

### --- Reservations (authenticated) ---

### Create reservation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/reservations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tableId": 2,
  "reservationTime": "2026-05-20T19:00:00",
  "duration": 90,
  "guestCount": 3
}

### My booking history
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/me/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### --- Admin ---

### All bookings
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/bookings
Authorization: Bearer {{adminLogin.response.body.token}}

### Update booking status
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/bookings/1
Authorization: Bearer {{adminLogin.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "CONFIRMED"
}

### List all tables (admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/tables
Authorization: Bearer {{adminLogin.response.body.token}}

### Create table
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/admin/tables
Authorization: Bearer {{adminLogin.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "tableNumber": 10,
  "capacity": 4,
  "status": "AVAILABLE"
}
